  3. Drawing model (cross-reference only — superseded by your new grammar)

  Captured from Groups.g before scope-out, because the mode flags are the directly-relevant idea: a path is operator +
  xOffset + yOffset? triples; current point defaults to frame origin. Modes: % = lengths as % of frame, ~ = relative (current
  point follows the pen), @ = move-to, : = close, ! = reset modes to pixel/absolute; d/u/l/r direction, R rotate, S scale, T
  translate; curves a/c/o = arc/bézier/oval. So the old model already had absolute + relative + percent coordinate modes as
  first-class flags — the concept worth carrying into the new grammar. The deeper architectural lesson sits in §4.

