  Why a Source lives on Bwana — answered. Selection is a global, observable broadcast channel. When you click a block, every
  block bound to "the current selection" must redraw — so instead of polling, they subscribe to a shared Source on the
  overseer (sELECTsource→addListener), and a selection write fires updateListeners→processReaction on each subscriber. The
  Sources live on Bwana specifically because they're process-global (one selection, one subscriber set), must outlive any
  window/layout pass, and are the rendezvous everyone can reach via use Control.bwana. That pattern is the old GUI's reactive
  system — a hand-rolled pub/sub keyed on selection. (selectedMembers = members-mode, selectedAttributes = attributes-mode,
  emptySource = null-object fallback, lastSelect = the value behind it all. And expandables is dead — declared, never used.)

